# PGML
#
#

BEGIN_PGML

[@ image( "21-R-KIN-ZA-30.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

The slender rod shown has a mass of [`m_{rod}=[$m]\:kg`], and is connected to a collar that slides on the curved bar shown. The bar is released
from rest at an angle of [`{\theta}=[$theta]\:^{\circ}`] in the position shown. If the radius of the curved slot is [`r=[$r]\:m`] and the coefficient of
kinetic friction between the rod and the floor is [`{\mu}_k=[$mu]`], find the acceleration of the rod.

[`a_G = `][_____]{"$agx"} [`\boldsymbol{\hat{i}}`] [`+`] [_____]{"$agy"} [`\boldsymbol{\hat{j}}`] [`m/s^2`]


END_PGML

